The Brief — licensing
======================

This repository mixes three kinds of material, and they are not under one license. Read
this before reusing anything.

1. The project's own writing — CC BY 4.0
----------------------------------------

All original text authored *by this project* is licensed under the Creative Commons
Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0).

  SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-4.0
  Full legal code: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode
  Human-readable summary: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

This covers: README.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, STRUCTURE.md, the files under methodology/ and
analysis/, the indices and templates, and the commentary sections of each entry
(Provenance, Confidence, Changes, Notes) — in short, everything in this archive that the
contributors wrote.

You are free to share and adapt this material for any purpose, including commercially,
provided you give appropriate credit to "The Brief" and link back to this repository.

